SUMMARY:AI Risks: Scams & Self-Harm with Russell Klein
DTSTAMP:20260624T010853Z
DTSTART:20260625T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Powerful AI is now available via websites\, apps and voice assi
	stants. This workshop addresses the gaps between what these system do and 
	the unsafe ways people commonly engage with them. \n\nWeaponization: How A
	I is used in scams\, impersonation and pressure tactics.\nFake media: Fake
	 images and recordings\, shared by friends and family\, increasingly misre
	presents the world we live in.\nExcessive trust: Why trusting advice from 
	an AI chatbot is a bad idea\, and how to do your research more safely.\nMe
	ntal Health: How AI chatbots and articulate-sounding\, robotic voices are 
	today leading the public to self-harm.\n\nThere is no charge for this tech
	 lecture presented by Russell Klein\, RK Media Services. You must RSVP to 
	register.\n\nhttps://www.erjcchouston.org/event/ai-risks-scams-self-harm-w
	ith-russell-klein/\n\nFrom ERJCC Houston
URL:https://www.erjcchouston.org/event/ai-risks-scams-self-harm-with-russel
	l-klein/
LOCATION:Herzstein Foundation Multipurpose Room
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:erjcc-houston
CATEGORIES:ERJCC Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
