SUMMARY:Houston Museum of Natural Science
DTSTAMP:20260624T010853Z
DTSTART:20260628T140000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Houston Museum of Natural Science comes to Levy Park to off
	er an opportunity to learn firsthand from Museum experts. Encounter real s
	pecimens and artifacts from the museum collection in an intimate\, educati
	onal atmosphere. \nMay 31: Rocks and Minerals \nExplore the fascinating ch
	aracteristics of the most important building blocks of Earth’s crust. \nJu
	ne 28: Ocean Life \nDive into Earth’s largest ecosystem and examine intrig
	uing examples of diverse ocean life. \nJuly 26: Energy \nExciting demonstr
	ations explore the remarkable forms of energy we encounter every day. \nAu
	gust 30: Dinosaur Discovery \nPeek into the thrilling daily life of the di
	nosaur: investigate what dinosaurs ate\, how they hunted\, and the adaptat
	ions they developed to survive in a harsh prehistoric world. \nSeptember 2
	7: Birds \nEncounter an amazing variety of birds and discover their fascin
	ating ancestral roots\, while learning about their adaptations for success
	. \nOctober 25: Ancient Egypt \nFrom mummies to the pyramids\, experience 
	amazing architectural and cultural aspects of Ancient Egypt. \nNovember 29
	: Little Bodies\, Big Jobs! \nBrings a selection of live arthropods from t
	he Cockrell Butterfly Center to your classroom. Audiences of all ages will
	 have a unique opportunity to meet some of the hardest workers in the inve
	rtebrate world up close and personal. \nDecember 13:  Astronomy  \nInvesti
	gate our place in space and ways we study this exciting place full of plan
	ets\, moons\, stars\, and galaxies.\n\nhttps://www.levyparkhouston.org/eve
	nts/houston-museum-of-natural-science/2026-06-28/\n\nFrom Levy Park Housto
	n
URL:https://www.levyparkhouston.org/events/houston-museum-of-natural-scienc
	e/2026-06-28/
LOCATION:Levy Park (Event Pavilion)\, TX
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:levy-park-houston
CATEGORIES:Levy Park Houston
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
